    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2005-09-22</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2005-10-04T17:28:18Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Requires the Secretary of Energy and the Secretary of Defense, within 90 days after enactment of this Act, to jointly designate three military installations closed pursuant to a base closure law as suitable for construction of an oil refinery.</p> <p>Prohibits the federal government, for two years, from selling or disposing of any such designated site except for purposes of oil refinery construction.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>To provide for the designation of 3 closed military installations as appropriate sites for construction of an oil refinery.</title>
